.SH NAME
cukes-vhs-init - Initialise config file for customisation


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcukes-vhs init [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Initialise a cukes-vhs config file for customisation.

.PP
Creates a config.tape file that can be customised to change VHS tape styling.
Use --force to overwrite an existing config file.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--force\fP[=false]
	Overwrite existing config file

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for init

.PP
\fB--output\fP="config/"
	Output directory for config file


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  cukes-vhs init                        # Create default config in config/
  cukes-vhs init --output my-config/    # Custom output directory
  cukes-vhs init --force                # Overwrite existing config
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcukes-vhs(1)\fP


